DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(&beginproblem);
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a=random(2, 9);
$soln1 = 1/(2*$a)*(1-1/100);
$soln2 = 1/(2*$a)*(1-1/10000);
$soln3 = 1/(2*$a);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));

Find the area under the curve
\( y = 1/($a x^3) \)
from \( x = 1\) to \( x = t \) and evaluate it for \( t = 10, t = 100 \).
Then find the total area under this curve for \( x \geq 1 \).
$BR
(a) t = 10
$BR \{ans_rule( 30) \}
$BR
EOT
&ANS(std_num_cmp($soln1));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
(b) t = 100
$BR \{ans_rule(30)\}
$BR
EOT
&ANS(std_num_cmp($soln2));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
(c) Total area
$BR \{ans_rule(30)\}
$BR
EOT
&ANS(std_num_cmp($soln3));

ENDDOCUMENT();
